Perhaps it was the excitement of the Grand National, but this horse fell at the first hurdle after wandering into thick mud.

It was hardly Becher's Brook - one of Aintree's most notorious fences - but Cody somehow found himself stuck in the bog in Belvedere, south-east London.

Crew members climbed into the watery ditch as they tried to ease the distressed animal to safety on Friday afternoon.

