Cody was covered head to hoof in mud after being dragged to safety, but - despite being shaken by the ordeal - was otherwise unharmed. 

Borough Commander for Bexley Richard Welch said crews worked hard to save the horse.

He added: 'One thing is certain that it won’t be running in the Grand National tomorrow.'

